# Styling Guidelines

## CSS Framework Integration
This project uses **Tailwind CSS** for utility classes and **PrimeReact** for component styling:

### Tailwind CSS Usage
- **Utility-first approach** for spacing, colors, and layout
- **Responsive design** with breakpoint prefixes (`md:`, `lg:`, `xl:`)
- **Custom utilities** defined in [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts)

### PrimeReact Styling
- **Theme configuration** in [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx)
- **Component-specific classes** for PrimeReact widgets
- **PrimeFlex integration** for grid and flex layouts

## Layout Patterns

### Container and Spacing
```typescript
// ✅ Good - Consistent container pattern
<div className="container mx-auto px-4 py-6">
  <div className="flex flex-column gap-4">
    {/* Content */}
  </div>
</div>
```

### Grid Layouts
```typescript
// ✅ Good - Responsive grid with PrimeFlex
<div className="grid">
  {products.map((product) => (
    <div key={product.id} className="col-12 md:col-6 lg:col-4 xl:col-3">
      <ProductCard product={product} />
    </div>
  ))}
</div>
```

